              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>brotherhood</Gloss>
                <Gloss>fellow believers</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It is often quite impossible to speak of fellow Christians as ‘the brothers and sisters,’ since a number of receptor languages do not permit this type of extension of meaning from an underlying base meaning ‘brother’ or ‘sister.’ Therefore, it may be necessary to speak of ‘fellow believers’ or ‘those who believe together with others’ or ‘those who likewise believe.’ See also discussion at {D:11.23}.</Comments>
